  "description": "An anthology of four standalone films encompassing different genres.<br>\n<br>\n<b>Tsukumo (Possessions)</b><br>\nA lost wanderer seeks refuge inside a shrine where he finds lots of possessed objects.<br>\n<br>\n<b>Hi no Youjin (Combustible)</b><br>\nThe movie depicts the events that led to the Great Fire of Meireki which destroyed more than half of the Japanese capital city of Edo.<br>\n<br>\n<b>Gambo (Gambo)</b><br>\nA young girl asks a white bear to defeat a vicious ogre that is kidnapping the first born girls of a small village.<br>\n<br>\n<b>Buki yo Saraba (A Farewell to Weapons)</b><br>\nIn a post-apocalyptic future, a group of soldiers is sent to a ghost city to destroy an automated sentry.<br>\n<br>\n<i>Note:<br>\n- Tsukumo and Hi no Youjin received advanced individual screenings at the Annecy Animation Film Festival in June 2012.<br>\n- Hi no Youjin and Buki yo Saraba are based on Katsuhiro Ootomo's manga of the same name, whereas Tsukumo and Gambo are original stories.</i>",
